4 I am sorry to see so many bad things said about Silverado.  Its one of my favorites.  I golf mostly in the afternoons.  We play at this course about 3 times a month.  Never had a problem.  My foursome even got to take off early.  One time my dad (age 85)  was late getting to the golf course.  When he arrived the staff loaded his clubs and him, up and brought him out to our hole where we were getting ready to tee off.  The course itself is pretty forgiving.  Pretty open in the front 9, little tighter on the back.  I recommend the Friday Night Fish Fry as well.  They have a great dinner and golf special.
